Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/LowerTierLocalAuthorityArea
Object: The geographic area in which a lower tier local authority may exercise its powers.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/
Object: A model describing geographic areas in the UK - being constituency areas, local authority areas, countries, and statistical regions within England - and the containment relationships between such areas.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/whollyContainedBy
Object: Relates a geographic area to the geographic area it is wholly contained by. A constituency area may be wholly contained by an upper tier local authority area. A constituency area may be wholly contained by a lower tier local authority area. A constituency area is wholly contained by a country. A constituency area in England is wholly contained by an English region. A lower tier local authority area may be wholly contained by a constituency area. A lower tier local authority area is wholly contained by an upper tier local authority area, except where the lower tier local authority area is the upper tier local authority area. An upper tier local authority area may be wholly contained by a constituency area. As at October 2021, an upper tier local authority area is wholly contained by a combined authority area, where such a combined authority area exists. An upper tier local authority area is wholly contained by a country. An upper tier local authority area in England is wholly contained by an English region. A combined authority area is wholly contained by the country of England. A combined authority area may be wholly contained by an English region. An English region is wholly contained by the country of England.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/StatutoryThing
Object: A statutory thing, for example: an Act of Parliament or a made statutory instrument.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/UpperTierLocalAuthorityArea
Object: The geographic area in which an upper tier local authority may exercise its powers.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/GeographicAreaEstablishedByStatute
Object: A geographic area established by an Act of Parliament or a made statutory instrument.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/ConstituencyArea
Object: The geographic area of a UK Parliament constituency.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/partlyContainedBy
Object: Relates a geographic area to the geographic area it is partly contained by. A constituency area may be partly contained by an upper tier local authority area. A constituency area may be partly contained by a lower tier local authority area. A lower tier local authority area may be partly contained by a constituency area. An upper tier local authority area may be partly contained by a constituency area. An upper tier local authority area may be partly contained by a combined authority area, though - as at October 2021 - this has not happened in practice.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/Region
Object: A statistical region in England corresponding to a NUTS level 1 region.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/Country
Object: A country in the United Kingdom.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/BoundarySet
Object: A boundary set for UK Parliament constituency areas, as proposed in a boundary review by the Boundary Commission and established by statute.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/CombinedAuthorityArea
Object: The geographic area in which a combined authority may exercise its powers.
